# syncfusion.rules.mdc

### A. Purpose
Define how every Syncfusion component is used in Angular across all Khwarizmi products. This file translates the design-system component map into Angular-specific implementation rules: `ejs-*` selectors, module imports, property binding syntax, RTL setup, and forbidden patterns.

The design-system component map (Figma Kit → Sf component name) lives in `components.rules.mdc`.
This file governs **how to write that code in Angular**.

---

### B. Angular Bootstrap — Required for Every Project

```typescript
// main.ts
import { bootstrapApplication } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { enableRtl, L10n, setCulture } from '@syncfusion/ej2-base';
import { registerLicense } from '@syncfusion/ej2-base';
import arLocale from './assets/locales/ar.json';
import { AppComponent } from './app/app.component';
import { appConfig } from './app/app.config';

// 1. License
registerLicense('YOUR_SYNCFUSION_LICENSE_KEY');

// 2. RTL + Arabic locale — always before bootstrapApplication
enableRtl(true);
setCulture('ar');
L10n.load({ ar: arLocale });

bootstrapApplication(AppComponent, appConfig);
```

```html
<!-- index.html root element -->
<html dir="rtl" lang="ar">
  <body class="e-khwarizmi">
    <!-- dark mode: add class="e-khwarizmi e-dark-mode" -->
    <app-root></app-root>
  </body>
</html>
```

```scss
/* styles.scss — global, not per-component */
@import '@syncfusion/ej2/material3.css';
```

**Rules:**
- `enableRtl(true)` must be called before `bootstrapApplication` — never inside a component.
- `setCulture('ar')` and `L10n.load()` must precede bootstrap — not in `ngOnInit`.
- Material-3 CSS imported once globally — never `@import` inside a component SCSS.
- Dark mode: toggle `.e-dark-mode` class on `<body>` or `<html>` — Syncfusion responds automatically.

