### E. RTL Rules (Angular-Specific)

```typescript
// ✅ Set globally in main.ts — never in components
enableRtl(true);

// ✅ RTL prop on individual components is not needed when set globally
// But can be set explicitly for hybrid LTR/RTL screens:
<ejs-grid [enableRtl]="true" />
```

- `enableRtl(true)` affects all Syncfusion component instances globally.
- Do not set `direction: rtl` on component host elements — Syncfusion handles it.
- Do not manually flip icon positions, padding, or margin for RTL — use logical CSS properties.
- `SfSidebar` with `enableRtl(true)` automatically positions to the right.
- `SfBreadcrumb` separator flips automatically.
- `SfTab` arrow navigation reverses automatically.

