### G. Accessibility Rules (Angular)

Syncfusion Material-3 components are WCAG 2.2 compliant by default. These rules cover what you must add on top:

```html
<!-- Icon-only buttons MUST have aria-label -->
<button ejs-button iconCss="e-icons e-delete" aria-label="حذف العنصر" />

<!-- Form fields — use floatLabelType or explicit label+id pair -->
<label for="search">بحث</label>
<ejs-textbox id="search" aria-label="بحث في السجلات" />

<!-- Live region for dynamic content updates -->
<div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" class="sr-only">
  {{ statusMessage() }}
</div>

<!-- Skip link — add at top of every page layout -->
<a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">تخطى إلى المحتوى الرئيسي</a>
<main id="main-content" tabindex="-1">
  ...
</main>
```

**Rules:**
- Never remove `aria-*` attributes added by Syncfusion to its components.
- Never set `tabindex="-1"` on Syncfusion components — it breaks keyboard navigation.
- Do not reimplement keyboard navigation — it is built into all Syncfusion components.
- `SfGrid` column `headerText` must be descriptive — never single-letter abbreviations.

---

### H. Do / Don't Summary

**Do:**
- ✅ Import only the Syncfusion Angular modules used in the component's `imports[]`
- ✅ Use `ejs-*` selectors with `[property]` binding — not HTML attributes
- ✅ Provide required grid services (`SortService`, etc.) in component `providers`
- ✅ Call `enableRtl(true)` + `setCulture('ar')` + `L10n.load()` in `main.ts`
- ✅ Import `material3.css` once in `styles.scss`
- ✅ Toggle `.e-dark-mode` on root element for dark theme
- ✅ Override Syncfusion tokens via CSS variables in `styles.scss`
- ✅ Scope `::ng-deep` overrides inside `:host` always
- ✅ Always generate empty state template for `ejs-grid`

**Don't:**
- ❌ Never use `SfGrid` without providing `SortService`, `FilterService`, `PageService`
- ❌ Never hardcode component dimensions — use tokens and fluid layout
- ❌ Never call `enableRtl()` inside a component lifecycle hook
- ❌ Never import Syncfusion CSS inside component SCSS — global only
- ❌ Never use `*ngFor` to loop Syncfusion list items — use `[dataSource]` binding
- ❌ Never re-implement what a Syncfusion component already does (validation, keyboard nav, ARIA)
- ❌ Never override `.e-*` class names directly without `:host ::ng-deep` scope
- ❌ Never use any non-Syncfusion component when a Syncfusion equivalent exists
